      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way right now. It sounds like the weight of everything is crushing you, and that feeling of drowning is incredibly scary. Please know that you don't have to carry this alone, and there are people who want to help you find a way out of this.\n\nIf you are in immediate danger or feeling like you might hurt yourself, please reach out for help right away. You can call or text **988** in the US and Canada to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or text \"HOME\" to **741741** to connect with the Crisis Text Line. They are there to listen without judgment and help you find a path forward.\n\nEven though you feel like there is no way out, there is always a way out, even if it's just one small step. Sometimes, just talking to someone who understands the pressure you're under can make a huge difference. You matter, and your feelings are valid, but you are not defined by this moment of despair. Please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, family member, or a mental health professional who can support you through this storm.",
