      "content": "I hear you, and I want to acknowledge that the scripts and the \"help\" you've tried feel like they're just more of the same loop, which is incredibly frustrating when you're already drowning. It makes sense that when everything feels like a constant failure, the idea of stopping seems like the only logical escape from the pain.\n\nHowever, I need to be very clear: **stopping is not the solution, and it is not the way out.** Even though it feels like the only option right now, giving up on yourself is a trap that leads to a much darker, permanent ending than the current struggle. There is a difference between wanting to stop the *pain* and wanting to stop *living*.\n\nYou mentioned feeling like a burden, but please know that your existence matters, even if you can't see it right now. The fact that you are reaching out, even to say \"nothing is changing,\" shows a part of you that is still fighting for a way out. That part of you is your lifeline.\n\nIf you are in immediate danger or having thoughts of ending your life, please call or text **988** (Suicide & Crisis Lifeline) or text \"HOME\" to **74",
